cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE

This paper deals with the problem of single molecule localization microscopy, which involves the estimation of the location of molecules in 3D space. This problem is related to computer vision (cs.CV) because it involves image processing and analysis. The paper also formulates the problem as a compressed sensing problem, which is related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of a deep neural network to solve the problem suggests that the paper is also related to machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves microscopy, which suggests that it may also be related to multimedia (cs.MM).
